Chantal Contouri https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chantal_Contouri 0 Chantal Contouri (born 8 April 1950) (sometimes credited as Chantal Cantouri, Greek: Σαντάλ Κοντούρης) is a Greek Australian television and film actress, best known for her role in the 1970s soap opera Number 96, as nurse Tracy Wilson, later revealed to be the serial killer known as the infamous "pantyhose strangler".
